      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sourdough starters are complex ecosystems, and inconsistency is very common! The unpredictable behavior is usually due to a fluctuating balance between the wild yeasts and lactic acid bacteria (LAB) in your starter. When it's super active, the yeasts are likely dominating, creating lots of gas. When it goes dormant, the bacteria might be producing more acid than the yeast can handle, or the microbial population might simply be resting during a less favorable feeding cycle.",
