      "content": "Think of it less as a battle and more as a shifting dynamic between two populations adapting to the available food and environment. If it smells overwhelmingly sour, pungent, or vinegary, the bacteria are likely winning the acid production war. If it just bubbles vigorously and smells yeasty, the yeast is leading the charge. You can try adjusting your feeding ratio, perhaps increasing the flour to water ratio slightly, which can dilute the existing acids and give the yeast a fresh start.",
